{
  "texts": [
    "This signifies something extremely important: Under the current AI and ML techniques and practices, there can never be an ASI, as these methods cannot create more information, which will then be embedded within the model.",
    "However, since most of these datasets contain a large amount of almost all human knowledge, it may be perceived as such by a large majority of the world.As a side note, it must be regarded that the main source of data for ML is the internet.",
    "After 2022 the AI content published online has increased and keeps doing so at an exponential rate.",
    "As time goes by, the AI created content will continue to flow and will dominate several fields, from art, video, music, science, up to everyday news.",
    "In a recent manuscript published in Nature, researchers showed that AI models collapse when trained on recursively generated data that come from AI [46]."
  ]
}